
Refactor the *Index page* to improve layout structure, UI consistency, and ensure full responsiveness across targeted desktop, tablet, and mobile devices. The page should render correctly without layout breaks, overlaps, or horizontal scrolling.

*Scope of Work:*

* Refactor existing HTML/CSS structure for better responsiveness and maintainability.
* Align UI components with responsive best practices (flex/grid).
* Ensure consistent spacing, typography, and component behavior across screen sizes.
* Validate responsiveness on the following devices and resolutions:

*Target Devices & Resolutions:*

*Desktop:*

* MacBook Pro 13-inch — *2560 × 1600*
* MacBook Air M2 (13.7-inch) — *2560 × 1664*

*Tablet:*

* iPad 11th Gen (2025) — *2360 × 1640*

*Mobile:*

* iPhone (multiple screen sizes)
* Android devices (standard and large screens)

*Functional Requirements:*

* No UI breakage or misalignment on any target resolution.
* No horizontal scroll on desktop or tablet views.
* Proper stacking and spacing of components on mobile.
* Buttons, forms, and interactive elements must remain fully accessible on all devices.

*Acceptance Criteria:*

* Index page adapts seamlessly across all specified resolutions.
* Responsive behavior verified using browser dev tools and real devices (where available).
* Layout remains consistent with approved UI/UX guidelines.
* No regression issues introduced in existing functionality.

*Out of Scope:*

* Feature changes or content updates (unless required for layout fixes).

